<br>
The &quot;race&quot; of a guild not on a rotation to try and kill something before the guild up for it gets to it is a non-issue. These proposals are nothing more than veiled attempts to limit content and limit the amount of time certain guilds have to wait between hitting Sev. It is about sharing, and the selfishness of some when it comes to sharing.<br>
<br>
Either have a rotation the way it is which is fair to EVERYONE because all have a chance to get on the rotation, and every guild gets the same amount of chances at sev per unit time, or put it off rotation. It boils down to nothing more than what was discussed on the thread about removing sev from rotation:<br>
<br>
Medium to medium-high guilds trying to get greater access to sev.<br>
<br>
In this case its just veiled in the bullshit story of &quot;keeping the rotation moving&quot;, so that small guilds that can't mobilize within a few hours can be forced to pass due to other guilds getting prepared and taking him out quickly after spawn (and its about at the point where any 2-group 60+ set of people that are decently equipped can take him out no problem), and large guilds that have more important mobs that won't mobilize within a few hours after spawn can be forced to passdue to other guilds getting prepared and taking him out quickly after spawn.<br>
<br>
The rotation is moving, and it doesn't make any difference whether you have 10 guilds inserted in a row or staggered, because a year from now all the guilds will have had the same number of shots at sev. I see this all too clearly as a few guilds to whom sev is a seriously important bottleneck in terms of guild progression at the moment due to the influx of new levels and equipment and skills with PoP making encounters easier looking for any way they can to get to sev quicker, at the expense of others.<br>
<br>
If you are that dang stuck, make it a guild priority to spend a week in tov farming SS armor and sell the MQs. 6-8 hours days in there for one week will net you the several hundred kpp it would take to buy a BoC. Don't try to do everything you can to get access to sev more over other people and try to cloak it in terms of &quot;fairness&quot;. Fairness means fairness to all. Hell, its not like the warrior epic proc really is even that good at generating hate, it isn't really, particularly when you have other melee equipped with weapons that do so much more raw damage that a couple of 14/24 weapons that even with the hate proc the MT is getting out-taunted.<br>
