Maybe, just maybe, the guild is off trying something new, or doing something else, and would rather wait a few hours, finish what they are in the middle of doing when sev popped, and then go kill him later when they are finished. That isn't &quot;bigger fish&quot;, as much as its &quot;other fish&quot;. The entire reasoning behind the 24 hour rule was so guilds will always have a chance to kill a mob during their prime time, so if they are doing something else they can finish it. Do you really expect us to accept that if you want to kill sev, you should have to be prepared to do nothing the day he is due or be willing to just evac from what you are currently doing and go kill him? What that effectively does is changes the 24 hour limit to much shorter time frame.<br>
<br>
It isn't an issue of having better stuff to do, its an issue of logistics and the fact you aren't going to just abandon a raid to do another raid when you don't have to. The statements weren't contradictions unless you want to pick apart the intent and try to force them to be.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Ok, I'll tell you what. You wait 2, 3 more months, tops, before the rotation for sev gets SO big, that people just say 'fuck it&quot; and go FFA on it. And then I say &quot;well, if people had been moving through the rotation at any kind of speed, maybe there would still BE a rotation&quot;. It's not QUITE as big as the list for Ragefire was, but it's getting there. What, 20 guilds at least now? More?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
