All the guilds that attempt to get on the rotation are obviously aware of the RTA, and the guidelines set forth by the community.  What if only one guild is allowed to enter the rotation per each spawn.  For instance guild A is up on rotation, guild B wants to enter rotation.  Guild B needs to check RTA to see who did last kill, and if it was a new guild entering rotation that did last kill, then they have to wait and attempt after guild A takes their turn.  If guild B reads that last kill was done by a guild already on the rotation, then they are able to attempt to enter the rotation.<br>
I think this will help new guilds enter rotation and yet still keep the rotation progressing.<br>
