Or how about this... Assume you have this rotation setup... Guild C, Guild B, Guild A.  Guild A is up for the kill, followed by Guild B, followed by Guild C.  If a guild (guild A) fails to kill him twice, the mob becomes a race between the guild A and the following guild on the rot (guild B) for any and all subsequent spawns until guild A kills him.  ONly those two guilds can participate in the race (or even talk it out and decide on who will get him) as well as any guild trying to enter the rotation of course.  If guild B kills him they move ahead of guild A on the rotation and then teh mob is a race between guild A and guild C, (guild C being the one following next on the list.)  Same rules apply.  So in essence, if a guild is not really interested in sev, the rotation rotates aroudn that guild, but they never lose their spot.  Just a though, not sure how well this woudl work however.   <p>Juryiel Shadowangel&lt;br&gt;<br>
